---

## Required Deliverables

### Documentation Files

1. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-governance-automation-index.md`**
   - Master overview of all governance automation
   - Links to scanner index, workflow index, evidence output index
   - How to navigate the governance system
   - How to find the scanner for a given governance area
   - How to add new scanners/automation to the index

2. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-scanner-index.md`**
   - Full index table for all known scanners/scripts
   - Columns for each entry:
     - Scanner name
     - Path
     - Purpose (one sentence)
     - Inputs (files/env vars consumed, no secrets)
     - Outputs (stdout format, evidence file written)
     - Flags supported (`--help`, `--markdown`, `--json`, `--strict`, `--live`)
     - Owner (role name)
     - Network required (yes/no)
     - Strict mode supported (yes/no)
     - Evidence file generated (path template)
     - Phase that introduced it
     - Exists in repo (yes/no — verified by executor)
   - GAP section: list missing scanners with recommended creation phase
   - Recommendations section: scanners that should be created or consolidated

3. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-workflow-index.md`**
   - Index of all GitHub Actions workflows related to Cloudflare governance
   - Columns:
     - Workflow file path
     - Workflow name
     - Trigger (push/PR/schedule/workflow_dispatch)
     - Purpose
     - Jobs
     - Scanners invoked
     - Evidence output
     - Owner
     - Phase introduced
   - Known workflow files to check (check if they exist):
     - `.github/workflows/cloudflare-release-readiness.yml`
     - `.github/workflows/deploy-worker.yml`
     - `.github/workflows/validate.yml`
     - `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
     - Any other workflow that invokes Cloudflare scripts
   - GAP section: workflows that should exist but do not

4. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-evidence-output-index.md`**
   - Index of all evidence documents and templates in the governance system
   - Sections:
     - Scanner output evidence (files generated by scanners)
     - Phase governance documents (docs/infra/ files per phase)
     - Templates (for release approval, incident review, etc.)
     - Evidence archive structure (Phase 16)
   - For each entry: path | purpose | format (md/json/yaml) | phase introduced | owner
   - GAP section: evidence outputs that should exist but do not

5. **`infra/cloudflare/README.md`** *(update)*
   - Add Phase 22 entry
   - Update master links table to reference governance automation index

